To create a fixed width webpage layout with two columns of different widths using Java code, you can use the CSS (Cascading Style Sheets) framework. Here's a simple example of how you can achieve this:

1. First, you'll need to set up your HTML structure. You can create a main div container that holds two child divs, one for each column:

```html
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Two Columns Layout</title>
    <style>
        body {
            display: flex;
            flex-direction: column;
            align-items: center;
            height: 100vh;
            margin: 0;
        }
        .main-container {
            display: flex;
            flex-wrap: wrap;
            justify-content: space-between;
            width: 2000px;
        }
        .column {
            width: 100%;
            max-width: 200px; /* This column will always be 200px wide */
        }
        .column1 {
            width: 830px; /* This column will be 830px wide */
        }
    </style>
</head>
<body>
