        <div class="column">Column 2</div>
    </div>
</body>
</html>
```

2. In this example, we're using Flexbox to create the layout. The main-container div is set to display as a flex container, and flex-direction is set to column to stack the child divs vertically. align-items: center is used to center the child divs vertically. The body's height is set to 100vh (100% of the viewport's height) to ensure the content takes up the full height of the screen.

3. The CSS classes ".column" and ".column1" are used to style the child divs. Both columns are set to have a width of 100% to ensure they span the full width of the main-container. However, we use the max-width property to limit the width of the first column to 200px, while the second column is set to 830px.

