END //
DELIMITER ;
```

2. Next, create another stored procedure that generates a non-rhyming poem using the 4 random words. You can use the `IF` condition to check if the last word in the poem matches the current word. If it does, the procedure will return an empty string.

```sql
DELIMITER //
CREATE PROCEDURE GetNonRhymingPoem()
BEGIN
  DECLARE @lastWord VARCHAR(255);
  SET @lastWord = '';
  DECLARE @poem VARCHAR(255);

  SELECT id, word INTO @lastWord, @poem
  FROM words
  ORDER BY RAND() LIMIT 1;

  IF @lastWord = '' THEN
    SET @poem = CONCAT(' ', @lastWord);
  ELSE
    SET @poem = CONCAT(' ', @lastWord, ' DOES NOT rhyme with ', @lastWord);
  END IF;

