- Flexibility to adapt to changing project requirements

Disadvantages of Kanban Boards:

- Requires more time and effort to set up and maintain
- Potential for information overload
- Dependency on a specific tool or process

In conclusion, incorporating agile methodologies in C++ projects within a limited timeframe requires careful consideration of the project requirements and team capabilities. While pair programming, automated testing and continuous integration, and Kanban boards offer potential benefits, they also have their respective drawbacks. It is essential to weigh the advantages and disadvantages of each approach and choose the most suitable one for the specific project and team.

